Blocks.childText: 288 SABDATH SCHOOL HYMNS. 3 Here may we, Lord, for ever share A peaceful, quiet haven; Whene'er oppress'd by worldly care We'll hasten to thy house of prayer, And find the joy of heaven. 4 And then shall life's last feeble ray Be calm as summer's even: While angels, hovering round, shall say Ye weary wanderers, come away, And be at rest in heaven." HYMN 322. L. M. Punctuality at School. THE clock has struck, I cannot stay, let me rise and haste away; I'll quit my bed, and leave my home, The hour of school at length is come. 2 I would be there when prayer begins, To seek the pardon of my sins; I'd ask the favor of the Lord, And pray to understand his word. 3 o, shall my teachers wait in vain, While my neglect must give them pain? No, let me rather strive to be The first that in the class they see. 4 These Sabbath days will soon be o'er, And I shall go to school no more: I would not then endure the pain Of having spent my time in vain. HYMN 323. 3 7s & 15. The Salbath School. HERE do children love to go, When the wintry tempests blow?
